description: Difference between the population sizes on 1 January of two consecutive years.

description: Exponential rate of change of the population over an annual period. It is calculated as ln(P2/P1) where P1 and P2 are the population sizes on 1 January of two consecutive years. It is expressed as a percentage.
indicatorDisplayName: Crude rate of total population change
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

description: The difference between the number of live births and the number of deaths during the year. A positive natural change, also known as natural increase, occurs when live births outnumber deaths. A negative natural change, also named as natural decrease, occurs when live births are less numerous than deaths.
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

indicator: Crude rate of natural change of population
description: The crude rate of natural change is the ratio of the natural change during the year (live births minus deaths) to the average population in that year. The value is expressed per 1 000 persons.
indicatorDisplayName: Crude rate of natural change of population
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

description: Number of persons per square Kilometer.
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

description: Number of live births over a given period divided by the person-years lived by the population over that period.

description: The average number of daughters a hypothetical cohort of women would have at the end of their reproductive period if they were subject during their whole lives to the fertility rates and the mortality rates of a given period. It is expressed as number of daughters per woman.

description: Expectation of life at age x is the average number of years remaining to be lived by those surviving to that age, based on a given set of age-specific rates of dying. It is derived by dividing the total person-years that would be lived beyond age x by the number of persons who survived to that age interval (Tx / lx).
indicatorDisplayName: Life expectancy at exact ages, Ex, by age groups and by sex
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

description: Expectation of life at age x is the average number of years remaining to be lived by those surviving to that age, based on a given set of age-specific rates of dying. It is derived by dividing the total person-years that would be lived beyond age x by the number of persons who survived to that age interval (Tx / lx).
indicatorDisplayName: Life expectancy at exact ages, Ex, by single age and by sex
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

indicator: Survivors to exact age l(x) - complete

sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

indicator: Age specific mortality rate m(x,n) - abridged
description: Central death rate for the age interval (x, x+n) where x is the initial age and n is the length of the interval. It is obtained as the ratio of the number of deaths by the number of person-years of exposure of the same age group (for a specified time period).
indicatorDisplayName: Age-specific mortality rates by age groups and by sex
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

indicator: Age specific mortality rate m(x,n) - complete
description: Central death rate between ages x and x + 1. It is obtained as the ratio of the number of deaths by the number of person-years of exposure of the same age interval (for a specified time period).
indicatorDisplayName: Age-specific mortality rates by single age and by sex
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

description: Probability of an individual age x dying before the end of the age interval (x, x+n) where n is the length of the interval.
indicatorDisplayName: Probability of dying by age groups and by sex
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

description: Probability of an individual age x dying between ages x and x + 1.
indicatorDisplayName: Probability of dying by single age and by sex
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

description: The ratio of the population under age x1 (e.g., 0-24) to the number of persons of working age x1-x2 (e.g., 25-64). It is expressed as number of dependants per 100 persons of working age (e.g., 25-64). Data are presented for different age categories.
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

description: The ratio of the population aged x2 and over (e.g., 65+) to the number of persons of working age x1-x2 (e.g., 25-64). It is expressed as number of dependants per 100 persons of working age (e.g., 25-64). Data are presented for different age categories.
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

description: The ratio of the number of persons of working age x1-x2 (e.g., 25-64) to the population aged x2 and over (e.g., 65+). It is expressed as number of persons of working age x1-x2 (e.g., 25-64 years) per person aged x2 years or over (e.g., 65+). Data are presented for different age categories.
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

description: The ratio of the sum of the population under age x1 (e.g., 0-24) and that aged x2 and over (e.g., 65+) to the number of persons of working age x1-x2 (e.g., 25-64). It is expressed as number of dependants per 100 persons of working age (e.g., 25-64). Data are presented for different age categories.
sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2024). World Population Prospects: The 2024 Revision, custom data acquired via website.
